sec.p:
As shown in Fig. 1e, the OER process is simply a reverse version of the ORR process (Table 1). By the reduction for O2 to H2O or OH, the ORR pathway could occur; meanwhile, by the H2O oxidation to O2 occurs through the OER pathway. Through numerous effects such as the electrode surface structure, materials with several facets, different reaction mechanisms could happen [99]. The most admitted OER overall reaction pathways include four discrete electron transfer stages, which are listed in Table 1, where * is the catalyst active site. The DFT computations outcomes expose that the HER process probably includes the Volmer–Heyrovsky or Volmer–Tafel route on a range of transition-metal surfaces, whereby the Volmer step is a fast reaction whereas the Heyrovsky or Tafel reaction is assigned to the rate-determining step [100, 101].Table 1
